Class JDocComment

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<Object>
          • com.helger.jcodemodel.JCommentPart
            • com.helger.jcodemodel.JDocComment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IJGenerable, IJObject, IJOwned, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<Object>, Collection<Object>, List<Object>, RandomAccess

    public class JDocComment
extends JCommentPart
implements IJGenerable, IJOwned
    JavaDoc comment.

    A javadoc comment consists of multiple parts. There's the main part (that comes the first in in the comment section), then the parameter parts (@param), the return part (@return), and the throws parts (@throws).
    TODO: it would be nice if we have JComment class and we can derive this class from there.
